CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 2, 1954, pg. 2 reads: "African Student Finds Welcome - Kwamena Dougan, a virtually penniless native of the Gold Coast in West Africa, this week found a gracious welcome and unexpected generosity in his quest to become an electrical engineer. Here he is with Dr. James B. Woodford, assistant professor of electrical engineering, in one of the electronics laboratories at famed Carnegie Tech. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Kwamena Dougan and Dr. James B. Woodford wearing double breasted suit, standing at large machine in electronics laboratory at Carnegie Tech
